There's places like japanese-online.com that have free basic lessons, that are pretty reliable and up to date. <br>
And then there is the book called Teach Yourself Japanese from the teach yourself series by Hellen Ballhatchet and Stefan Kaiser. It's under 10 dollars and has vocab, sentence structure, and basic conversation...<br>
For free sources, you can probably sit in on some japanese classes at a local community college or university, just don't get caught....<br>
