<br>
1) pick up a Japanese dictionary of foreign words, or have a knowledgeable friend write out a list of foreign words in Japanese.  The point is, Japanese has over 500 words dierctly borrowed from English, with a little Japanese accent added to spice things up.  For example, TABLE is teeburu.<br>
<br>
When you['re just starting out, your lack of vocabulary is a huge, daunting mountain in front of you, and a major interest-killer.  If, on the other hand, you can start with the secure knowledge that your English background has ALREADY taught you over 500 words in Japanese... well, that's a HECK of a jump-start, and quite a morale-booster.<br>
<br>
2) Label everything in your house.  Start with NOUNS like REIZOKO (fridge), NAGASHI (sink/faucet), and so on.  Put ONLY the Japanese on the front, and put the English translation on the back, but make sure you can't read the English through semi-clear paper.<br>
<br>
Colored post-its are pretty good for this, but the glue wears off quickly.  A better choice is index cards, bent into little tents that can sit on the object, or taped to the object.  Get colored index (3&quot;x5&quot;) cards, if you can.<br>
<br>
Make sure you and your kids SAY these names whenever they use the objects, or even as you pass the objects.  Make a game of it... run around the house with them, playing speed-speech or noun-tag.<br>
<br>
When you're fairly comfortable with the nouns, start to use them instead of the English words, when you speak to your children.<br>
<br>
After everyone's comfortable with the nouns, put more words on the objects.... adjectives (hot, cold, loud...) or verbs (open, turn on, ...), this time.  <br>
<br>
Last, at the end of about 2 or 3 months, put up FULL SENTENCES.  (I open the refrigerator.  The orange juice is cold and sweet....)  Make the sentences SILLY, TOO, to maintain the kids' interest.  For example, &quot;Please don't put the cat in the microwave.&quot;<br>
<br>
Your neighbors will think you're crazy, and it adds to the clutter of your house, but you WILL learn Japanese... quickly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=974.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=974.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=974.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=974.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.threadControl?topicID=974.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=974.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=974.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="